## API & Data Fetching (store/api)
All backend API calls go through RTK Query slices in `store/api/`. Do not add ad-hoc fetch/axios calls; use or extend existing API slices.

### Setup (lib/api.ts)
- **baseUrl**: `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` (default `http://localhost:8001/api/`)
- **baseQuery**: `fetchBaseQuery` with `prepareHeaders` that attach `Authorization: Bearer <session.accessToken>` from NextAuth `getSession()`
- **baseQueryWithRetry**: Wraps baseQuery; on 401 calls `signOut()` and redirects to `/auth/login`; normalizes success to `{ success: true, data }` and errors to `{ success: false, errors }` so components see a consistent shape
- **API_ENDPOINTS**: Single source of path strings (e.g. `API_ENDPOINTS.HOTELS.BASE`, `API_ENDPOINTS.HOTELS.DETAIL(id)`). Add new endpoints here, then use in API slices

### API slices (store/api/*.ts)
- Use `createApi` from `@reduxjs/toolkit/query/react` with `baseQuery: baseQueryWithRetry`
- Set `reducerPath` (e.g. `"hotelApi"`) and `tagTypes` for cache invalidation
- Define endpoints with `builder.query` (GET) or `builder.mutation` (POST/PATCH/DELETE)
- Type responses as `ApiResponse<T>` or `PaginatedApiResponse<T>` from `@/lib/types` or `@/lib/types/http`; backend returns camelCase (Django camelCase renderer)
- For query params the backend expects in snake_case (e.g. search), build `URLSearchParams` in the `query` fn and map camelCase → snake_case (e.g. `minRating` → `min_rating`)
- Use `providesTags` and `invalidatesTags` so list/detail caches stay in sync after mutations
- Export generated hooks (e.g. `useGetHotelQuery`, `useUpdateHotelMutation`) from each slice
- Register each slice in `store/store.ts`: add reducer and middleware for every API slice

### Using in components
- Prefer `useXxxQuery` / `useXxxMutation` hooks; use `skip` or conditional args to avoid unnecessary requests
- Handle `isLoading`, `isError`, `error`, `data`; for success, use `data?.data` when the backend wraps in `{ success, data }` (baseQueryWithRetry keeps that shape)
- For paginated lists, use `data?.results`, `data?.count`, `data?.next`/`previous` from `PaginatedApiResponse<T>`

### Types
- Keep request/response types in `lib/types/` (hotel, user, auth, facility, http, etc.) in camelCase to match backend
- Use `ApiResponse<T>`, `PaginatedApiResponse<T>`, and `ApiError` from `lib/types` or `lib/types/http`

## Data Patterns
- All server data from the Django backend is fetched via `store/api` RTK Query slices (see API & Data Fetching above)
- Use proper loading states (`isLoading`, `isFetching`) and error handling (`isError`, `error`) from RTK Query hooks
- Use proper TypeScript types from `lib/types/` for all API data (camelCase)
- Rely on RTK Query caching and tag invalidation; avoid duplicate requests (e.g. skip initial effect runs that re-push same params)

## Charts & Visualizations
- Use Recharts library (already configured in template)
- Follow existing chart component patterns
- Make all charts responsive and accessible
- Use consistent color schemes across charts
- Include proper tooltips and legends

## API Route Patterns
- App data is served by the Django backend; the frontend calls it via RTK Query in `store/api` using `API_ENDPOINTS` and `baseQueryWithRetry` (see API & Data Fetching)
- For any Next.js API routes (e.g. auth callbacks, webhooks), follow App Router API route structure, proper HTTP methods, and consistent response formats

